Now we see that the underlying translation symmetry does not require the
single-particle hopping Hamiltonian  to have a translation symmetry.
It only require  to be invariant under the  PSG or the 
PSG. When  is invariant under the  PSG, the hopping Hamiltonian
has the usual translation symmetry. When  is invariant under the
 PSG, the hopping Hamiltonian has a magnetic translation symmetry
describing a hopping in a magnetic field with -flux through each odd
plaquette.

