symmetry. The masslessness of the Dirac fermion is protected by the quantum
order and the associated PSG.


QED and QCD 
from a bosonic model on cubic lattice 

In this section, we are going to generalize the results in RS8909  and
Wlight  and use a bosonic model on cubic lattice to generate QED and QCD
with  families of massless quarks and leptons.
To describe the local Hilbert space on site  in our bosonic model, it is
convenient to introduce fermions  and ,
where ,  
